398
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:33,800
 Tianqi City was besieged by bloodshed and everyone was on edge.

399
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:37,400
 This period came to be known as the Six Princes' Struggle for Power.

400
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:42,100
 To fend off these mysterious assassins, Xiao Ruofeng - Prince Langya,

401
00:33:42,100 --> 00:33:44,500
 Li Xinyue -  Successor of the Heart Sword,

402
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:46,000
 Ji Ruofeng - Wuji Staff

403
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,800
 Tang Lianyue of the Tang Clan,

404
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,700
 and Sikong Changfeng of Xueyue City

405
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:52,800
 established the Internal Guard Office of Tianqi.

406
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:59,300
 They joined forces to restore peace to Tianqi City after a brief period of turmoil.

407
00:33:59,300 --> 00:34:04,600
 These four people were then known as the Four Guardians of Tianqi.

408
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,600
 Just as the chaos began to subside,

409
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:08,900
 Emperor Tai'an suddenly fell gravely ill and was fading fast.

410
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:13,000
 The six princes, under the lead of Prince Qing, conspired and initiated a coup.

411
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:17,700
 They fought their way to Pingqing Hall and demanded the throne from Emperor Tai'an.

412
00:34:17,700 --> 00:34:22,600
 Xiao Ruofeng led the Four Guardians of Tianqi and Tiger Army to quell the coup

413
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:25,800
